#. <section class="sutta" id="an4.57"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an4.57:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.57:0.2"
msgid "6. Puññābhisandavagga"
msgstr "6. Overflowing Merit"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an4.57:0.3"
msgid "57. Suppavāsāsutta"
msgstr "57. Suppavāsā"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.63"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: pajjanikaṃ → sajjanelaṃ (bj, pts1) | pajjanelaṃ (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: koliyānaṃ → koḷiyānaṃ (pts1)
msgctxt "an4.57:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā koliyesu viharati pajjanikaṃ nāma koliyānaṃ nigamo."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Koliyans, where they "
"have a town named Pajjanika."

msgctxt "an4.57:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena "
"suppavāsāya koliyadhītuyā nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte "
"āsane nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went "
"to the home of Suppavāsā the Koliyan, where he sat on the seat spread out."

msgctxt "an4.57:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho suppavāsā koliyadhītā bhagavantaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena "
"sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi."
msgstr ""
"Then Suppavāsā served and satisfied the Buddha with her own hands with a "
"variety of delicious foods."

msgctxt "an4.57:1.4"
msgid ""
"Atha kho suppavāsā koliyadhītā bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ "
"ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"When the Buddha had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, she sat down to one "
"side."

msgctxt "an4.57:1.5"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho suppavāsaṃ koliyadhītaraṃ bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said to her:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an4.57:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Bhojanaṃ, suppavāse, dentī ariyasāvikā paṭiggāhakānaṃ cattāri ṭhānāni deti."
msgstr ""
"“Suppavāsā, when a noble disciple gives food, she gives the recipients four "
"things."

msgctxt "an4.57:2.2"
msgid "Katamāni cattāri?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "an4.57:2.3"
msgid "Āyuṃ deti, vaṇṇaṃ deti, sukhaṃ deti, balaṃ deti."
msgstr "Long life, beauty, happiness, and strength."

msgctxt "an4.57:2.4"
msgid "Āyuṃ kho pana datvā āyussa bhāginī hoti dibbassa vā mānusassa vā."
msgstr "Giving long life, she has long life as a god or human."

msgctxt "an4.57:2.5"
msgid "Vaṇṇaṃ datvā vaṇṇassa bhāginī hoti dibbassa vā mānusassa vā."
msgstr "Giving beauty, she has beauty as a god or human."

msgctxt "an4.57:2.6"
msgid "Sukhaṃ datvā sukhassa bhāginī hoti dibbassa vā mānusassa vā."
msgstr "Giving happiness, she has happiness as a god or human."

msgctxt "an4.57:2.7"
msgid "Balaṃ datvā balassa bhāginī hoti dibbassa vā mānusassa vā."
msgstr "Giving strength, she has strength as a god or human."

msgctxt "an4.57:2.8"
msgid ""
"Bhojanaṃ, suppavāse, dentī ariyasāvikā paṭiggāhakānaṃ imāni cattāri ṭhānāni "
"detīti."
msgstr ""
"When a noble disciple gives food, she gives the recipients these four things."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
#. VAR: Susaṅkhataṃ → saṅkhataṃ (s1-3)
#. VAR: dadāti → yāva deti (s1-3)
msgctxt "an4.57:3.1"
msgid "Susaṅkhataṃ bhojanaṃ yā dadāti,"
msgstr "When she gives well-prepared food,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: paṇītaṃ → supaṇītaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an4.57:3.2"
msgid "Suciṃ paṇītaṃ rasasā upetaṃ;"
msgstr "pure, fine, and full of flavor,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.57:3.3"
msgid "Sā dakkhiṇā ujjugatesu dinnā,"
msgstr "that offering—given to people of integrity,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.57:3.4"
msgid "Caraṇūpapannesu mahaggatesu;"
msgstr "who have good conduct, and are big-hearted—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.57:3.5"
msgid "Puññena puññaṃ saṃsandamānā,"
msgstr "joins merit to merit. It’s very fruitful,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.57:3.6"
msgid "Mahapphalā lokavidūna vaṇṇitā."
msgstr "and is praised by those who know the world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an4.57:4.1"
msgid "Etādisaṃ yaññamanussarantā,"
msgstr "Those who recall such sacrifices,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.57:4.2"
msgid "Ye vedajātā vicaranti loke;"
msgstr "live in the world full of joy."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.57:4.3"
msgid "Vineyya maccheramalaṃ samūlaṃ,"
msgstr "They’ve driven out the stain of stinginess down to the root,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an4.57:4.4"
msgid "Aninditā saggamupenti ṭhānan”ti."
msgstr "blameless, they go to a heavenly place.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.57:4.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
